## GitHub Actions: 54. Workflow Inputs and Outputs

**Workflow inputs and outputs** are used to pass values into a workflow and send values from one job/workflow to another.

## 1. Workflow Inputs

Inputs are values given to a workflow when it runs.

They are commonly used with:

```yaml
workflow_dispatch
workflow_call
```

## Example: Manual Workflow Input

```yaml
name: Manual Deploy Workflow

on:
  workflow_dispatch:
    inputs:
      environment:
        description: Select deployment environment
        required: true
        default: dev
        type: choice
        options:
          - dev
          - staging
          - production

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Print Environment
        run: echo "Deploying to ${{ inputs.environment }}"
```

## Explanation

When we run this workflow manually from GitHub Actions tab, GitHub asks us to select an environment.

Example:

```text
dev
staging
production
```

If we select `production`, output will be:

```text
Deploying to production
```

## 2. Workflow Outputs

Outputs are values generated by one job and used by another job.

## Example: Job Output

```yaml
name: Workflow Outputs Example

on: push

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    outputs:
      app-version: ${{ steps.version.outputs.version }}

    steps:
      - name: Generate Version
        id: version
        run: echo "version=1.0.5" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT

  deploy:
    needs: build
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Use Build Output
        run: echo "Deploying version ${{ needs.build.outputs.app-version }}"
```

## Explanation

In the `build` job:

```yaml
echo "version=1.0.5" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
```

creates a step output.

Then job output is created:

```yaml
app-version: ${{ steps.version.outputs.version }}
```

In the `deploy` job, we use:

```yaml
${{ needs.build.outputs.app-version }}
```

Output:

```text
Deploying version 1.0.5
```

## Real-Time Example: Build and Deploy

```yaml
name: Build and Deploy with Inputs Outputs

on:
  workflow_dispatch:
    inputs:
      environment:
        description: Deployment environment
        required: true
        default: staging
        type: string

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    outputs:
      artifact-name: ${{ steps.artifact.outputs.name }}

    steps:
      - name: Checkout Code
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Build Application
        run: mvn clean package

      - name: Set Artifact Name
        id: artifact
        run: echo "name=myapp-${{ inputs.environment }}.jar" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT

  deploy:
    needs: build
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Deploy Application
        run: |
          echo "Environment: ${{ inputs.environment }}"
          echo "Artifact: ${{ needs.build.outputs.artifact-name }}"
```

## Simple Definition

**Workflow inputs receive values from users or other workflows, and workflow outputs send generated values from one job or workflow to another.**
